<font color="#FF0000">CORPSMEN....</font><br>
<tt>Mon Jan  6 23:30:37 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Although I wasn't a Viet Nam era corpsman, (I served in the NAvy from 1983 to 1994 as one) I knew quite a few through my early years in the Navy.<br><br>
They shared their experiences, and tried to teach us well for &quot;the next one&quot;.<br>
 <br>
In 1990 I returned from the Persian Gulf after flying Medevac for 11 months...  Every word they ever uttered was not enough to prepare me for the life of a &quot;combat medic&quot;  ...  I could never pretend to walk in the shoes of these men who served before me.<br>
 <br>
Even though the Gulf was a &quot;little war&quot; (I say this jokingly, no war is little, no war forgivable in my eyes)  It showed me what kind of men these men were... <br>
 <br>
I take my hat off to each and every one of them...<br>

